I had missed it, so I got excited to go check it out again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="https://www.google.com/logos/doodles/2017/s-chandrasekhars-107th-birthday-5671696282419200-2xa.gif" src="https://www.google.com/logos/doodles/2017/s-chandrasekhars-107th-birthday-5671696282419200-2xa.gif"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The doodle is amazing! It illustrates the concept of a star when it gains 1.4
times the mass of sun will turn into white-dwarf and eventually into a
black-hole!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chandrasekhar discovered this, and it is known as Chandrasekhar's limit.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>physics</category><guid>http://www.xtoinfinity.com/posts/2017/10/20/s-chandrasekhars-107th-birthday.html</guid><pubDate>Fri, 20 Oct 2017 20:40:11 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>